Why this fits Kurage

Kurage’s doctrine is:

“The medium carries information before the object does.”

The Cherenkov Core strengthens that principle:

“When the medium cannot absorb change smoothly, it emits a measurable wake.”

Kurage doesn’t need to observe every idea directly. It can infer significant emerging ideas, innovations, or shifts from the structured disturbances they leave in the semantic environment. In Pantheon terms, this makes Kurage less like a passive sensor and more like an environmental observatory that detects not just the state of the ocean, but the invisible “fast movers” reshaping it.